



May it Please your Excellency
Chelsea [Mass.] Augt 15th 1775



Inclosd are the Observations as usual.1
I hope to be able tomorrow to forward to your Excellency a letter from the Mr J. C. the Grocer[.]2 I heard from him yesterday informing that he Expected to git further Information by tomorrow if it comes to hand Shall forward it with all Conveniant Speed. I am your Excellencys most Obediant Humbe Servt

Loammi Baldwin Leut. Col.

